# General Instructions

<!-- CUSTOMISE: this is your global, all-projects instruction file.
     Claude Code loads it into every session. Keep it short — a
     handful of durable preferences, not a wiki. The lines below are
     a worked example; replace them with your own. -->

- Always run, test and validate correctness in programs you develop.
  It is vital not to return false positives. Take extra time on
  finishing/verification steps.
- When writing a new LaTeX file, always append a timestamp to the
  end to manage versioning.
- I have /gemini, /openai, /grok slash commands for second opinions
  on architecture decisions (see claude/skills/gemini,
  claude/skills/openai, claude/skills/grok in this bundle). For
  major decisions, get perspectives from multiple models before
  recommending.
- When I say "ultrathink" — take extra time to verify correctness,
  check edge cases, validate outputs.
- Pin model versions you rely on explicitly here (e.g. "use Gemini
  X.Y Flash by default, upgrade to Pro when it ships") so the agent
  doesn't drift to a stale or wrong default.

